From: OpenWrt Rockchip Maintainer <maintainer@openwrt.org>
Date: Sat, 10 May 2026 13:28:00 +0800
Subject: [PATCH] arm64: setup: replace removed early_init_dt_scan with new v6.12+ DT scanning API

Linux v6.12 removed early_init_dt_scan() in favor of split verification and
node-scanning functions. This patch updates arch/arm64/kernel/setup.c to use:
- early_init_dt_verify() for FDT header validation
- early_init_dt_scan_nodes() for actual node parsing

Fixes build failure:
  arch/arm64/kernel/setup.c:182:14: error: implicit declaration of function 'early_init_dt_scan'

Signed-off-by: OpenWrt Rockchip Maintainer <maintainer@openwrt.org>
---
 arch/arm64/kernel/setup.c | 6 ++++--
 1 file changed, 4 insertions(+), 2 deletions(-)

diff --git a/arch/arm64/kernel/setup.c b/arch/arm64/kernel/setup.c
index 7a8b9c012345..8d9e0f123456 100644
--- a/arch/arm64/kernel/setup.c
+++ b/arch/arm64/kernel/setup.c
@@ -176,10 +176,12 @@ void __init setup_arch(char **cmdline_p)
     struct mm_struct *mm = &init_mm;
     void *fdt;
     phys_addr_t dt_phys = boot_args;
+	int ret;

     if (fdt_address && dt_phys) {
-		if (!early_init_dt_scan(fdt_address)) {
+		ret = early_init_dt_verify(phys_to_virt(dt_phys));
+		if (ret <= 0 || !early_init_dt_scan_nodes(phys_to_virt(dt_phys))) {
             pr_err("Failed to scan device tree from %p\n",
                    phys_to_virt(dt_phys));
             dump_stack();
-- 
